<heading box="[136,931,1654,1681]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" reason="3">
<taxonomicName authority="M.D.Miranda &amp; E.L.Jacques" authorityName="M. D. Miranda &amp; E. L. Jacques. A, Abaxial" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,675,1654,1681]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,341,1654,1681]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Begonia atlantica</emphasis>
M.D.Miranda &amp; E.L.Jacques
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[687,773,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[687,773,1655,1681]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[789,866,1654,1681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1767,1789]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,209,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[215,1371,209,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–L. Begonia atlantica M.D.Miranda &amp; E.L.Jacques. A, Abaxial leaf surface; B, Adaxial leaf surface; C, Inflorescence showing pistillate and staminate flower; D, Inflorescence showing staminate flowers; E, Staminate flower, anterior view; F, Staminate flower, lateral view; G, Staminate flower, posterior view; H, Pistillate flower, anterior view; I, Pistillate flower, lateral view; J, Pistillate flower, posterior view; K, Ovary, cross section; L, Immature fruit. (Scale Bars: A–B= 6.5 cm; C= 4 cm; D= 3 cm; E= 1.6 cm; F= 1.6 cm; G= 0.8 cm; H= 1.6 cm; I= 2 cm; J= 0.8 cm; K= 0.7 cm; L= 1.2 cm). (A–L from M.D.Miranda 12)." pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[880,896,1655,1681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,190,1858]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–G. Begonia atlantica M.D.Miranda &amp; E.L.Jacques. A, Habit; B, Plants in their habitat with staminate and pistillate flower at anthesis; C, Detail of the stem and petioles, showing their indumentum; D, Young plants growing on rock; E, Plant at the earliest flowering time; F, Detail of the stipule, highlighting its indumentum; G, Inflorescence with a staminate flower at anthesis and immature pistillate and staminate flower. (A–G from M.D.Miranda 12)." pageId="0" pageNumber="147">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[908,922,1655,1681]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1767,1789]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,212,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1436,190,1743]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Begonia atlantica M.D.Miranda &amp; E.L.Jacques (red dot) in the Caraguatatuba municipality." pageId="0" pageNumber="147">3</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="147" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1730,1896]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,241,1730,1752]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. D. Miranda &amp; E. L. Jacques. A, Abaxial" authorityYear="2022" box="[246,417,1730,1752]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[246,417,1730,1752]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Begonia atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="M. D. Miranda (2021: 49)" authorityName="M. D. Miranda. A, Young" authorityPageNumber="49" authorityYear="2021" box="[613,1061,1730,1752]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microinduta">
<emphasis box="[613,815,1730,1752]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Begonia microinduta</emphasis>
M.D. 
<bibRefCitation author="Miranda, M. D." box="[866,1061,1730,1752]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" pagination="49 - 53" refId="ref4531" refString="Miranda, M. D. (2021) Begonia microinduta (Begoniaceae) a new species from the Atlantic Coastal Forest in the state of Sao Paulo, Brazil. Phytotaxa 497 (1): 49 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 497.1.5" type="journal article" year="2021">Miranda (2021: 49)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs chiefly in having villous stems (
<emphasis box="[197,217,1767,1788]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">vs</emphasis>
. glabrous) and a ciliate leaf margin (
<emphasis box="[571,591,1767,1788]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">vs</emphasis>
. not ciliate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
