<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,158,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,398,1454,1480]" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. D. Miranda &amp; E. L. Jacques. A, Abaxial" authorityYear="2022" box="[426,626,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[426,626,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">Begonia atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="E. L. Jacques (2019: 57)" authorityName="E. L. Jacques" authorityPageNumber="57" authorityYear="2019" box="[768,1185,1454,1481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="itaipeensis">
<emphasis box="[768,918,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">B. itaipeensis</emphasis>
E.L. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacques, E. L." box="[967,1185,1454,1481]" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" pagination="57 - 62" refId="ref4233" refString="Jacques, E. L. (2019) Begonia itaipeensis (Begoniaceae), a new species endemic to Atlantic Coastal Forest in the state of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Phytotaxa 425 (1): 57 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 425.1.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Jacques (2019: 57)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="E. L. Jacques (2020: 39)" authorityName="E. L. Jacques" authorityPageNumber="39" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lorenzii">
<emphasis box="[1195,1310,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">B. lorenzii</emphasis>
E.L.Jacques (2020: 39)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="M. D. Miranda (2021: 49)" authorityName="M. D. Miranda. A, Young" authorityPageNumber="49" authorityYear="2021" box="[271,730,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microinduta">
<emphasis box="[271,440,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">B. microinduta</emphasis>
M.D. 
<bibRefCitation author="Miranda, M. D." box="[501,730,1490,1516]" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" pagination="49 - 53" refId="ref4531" refString="Miranda, M. D. (2021) Begonia microinduta (Begoniaceae) a new species from the Atlantic Coastal Forest in the state of Sao Paulo, Brazil. Phytotaxa 497 (1): 49 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 497.1.5" type="journal article" year="2021">Miranda (2021: 49)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. B. Sm. ex S. F. Sm. &amp; Wassh. (1999: 27)" authorityName="S. F. Sm. &amp; Wassh." authorityPageNumber="27" authorityYear="1999" box="[787,1415,1490,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="windischii">
<emphasis box="[787,935,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">B. windischii</emphasis>
L.B.Sm. ex S.F.Sm. &amp; Wassh. (1999: 27)
</taxonomicName>
by having three tepals in the pistillate flowers; this is not a common characteristic in Brazilian 
<taxonomicName box="[1160,1341,1526,1552]" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis box="[1160,1253,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">Begonia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jacques, E. L." pageId="1" pageNumber="148" pagination="57 - 62" refId="ref4233" refString="Jacques, E. L. (2019) Begonia itaipeensis (Begoniaceae), a new species endemic to Atlantic Coastal Forest in the state of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Phytotaxa 425 (1): 57 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 425.1.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Jacques, 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. D. Miranda. A, Young" authorityYear="2021" box="[218,456,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microinduta">
<emphasis box="[218,456,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">Begonia microinduta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by its narrow leaves with a cuspidate apex; pubescent petioles, and leaf veins on the abaxial surface and peduncles covered with short microscopic trichomes. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. D. Miranda &amp; E. L. Jacques. A, Abaxial" authorityYear="2022" box="[1169,1371,1598,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[1169,1371,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">Begonia atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. D. Miranda. A, Young" authorityYear="2021" box="[198,365,1634,1660]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microinduta">
<emphasis box="[198,365,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">B. microinduta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a smaller stature ca. 
<quantity box="[714,811,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="4.0">4–21 cm</quantity>
tall (
<emphasis box="[871,894,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[908,1024,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="cm" value="39.5" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="19.0">19–60 cm</quantity>
); villous stems (
<emphasis box="[1208,1231,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. glabrous); stipules pilose on the midrib and close to the margins, with simple trichomes (
<emphasis box="[923,946,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. pilose only on the midrib, with microscopic trichomes); villous petioles, hairs ca. 
<quantity box="[551,615,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long (
<emphasis box="[686,709,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. pubescent, with hairs less than 
<quantity box="[1067,1131,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long), coriaceous leaves (
<emphasis box="[1421,1444,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. membranaceous); and a ciliate leaf margin (
<emphasis box="[637,660,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. not ciliate; 
<figureCitation box="[805,874,1742,1769]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[136,229,1958,1980]" captionTargetBox="[168,1432,202,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,190,1934]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution map of Begonia umbrosa M.D.Miranda &amp; E.L.Jacques (star)." pageId="1" pageNumber="148">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. D. Miranda &amp; E. L. Jacques. A, Abaxial" authorityYear="2022" box="[897,1098,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[897,1098,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">Begonia atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1451,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="windischii">
<emphasis box="[1304,1451,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">B. windischii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having staminate flowers with a pilose indumentum externally, with simple and 2-branched trichomes. It can be distinguished by its smaller stature (
<quantity box="[533,630,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="4.0">4–21 cm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[636,659,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[672,782,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="cm" value="39.5" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="19.0">19–60 cm</quantity>
tall); pilose stems (
<emphasis box="[997,1020,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. glabrous); shorter internodes (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="cm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2.5 cm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[179,202,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[217,349,1850,1877]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="148" unit="cm" value="2.85" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–4.5 cm</quantity>
); its densely pilose indumentum of the petioles (
<emphasis box="[903,926,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. scarcely pilose in upper portions, with a ring of trichomes at the stem close to the base of the petiole and at the apex); its leaves with cuspidate apices (
<emphasis box="[1344,1367,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. acute) and ciliate margins (
<emphasis box="[368,391,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. not ciliate), and flat veins on both leaf surfaces (
<emphasis box="[955,978,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. prominent on both leaf surfaces); and its staminate tepals, which are externally pubescent, except in the upper third, (
<emphasis box="[988,1011,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="148">vs</emphasis>
. pilose in the center).
</paragraph>
